    <data key="d0">EcoFit: Responsive Lambda-based Microservices at Scale</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DnTQ3matqts</data>
    <data key="d2">EcoFit provides automated asset tracking for the fitness industry, placing sensors on gym equipment to track utilization. The data is processed in the cloud to generate reports for gym chains, helping them with purchasing decisions and equipment rotation. The architecture transitioned from monolithic EC2 applications to a serverless model to address scalability issues encountered with 100-500 facilities. Key design decisions include extensive use of AWS IoT services for edge processing (Greengrass) and real-time data ingestion (IoT Core, API Gateway), serverless compute (Lambda) for data processing and reporting, and a time series database for core data storage. The system also includes robust monitoring for sensor and gateway health with automated alerting via SQS and SNS, and an installer app for system deployment and configuration.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
